# Partie C Statistics a deux variables Partie C1 Croisment de deux variables qualitatives Tableau et histogramme des effectifs 
{r}

table(sexe, transportTravail, deparse.level = 2, useNA = "always")
N = table(sexe, transportTravail)
addmargins(N)

# Histogramme empile par default avec legende placee
barplot(N,col=c("orange","green"),legend=T)
barplot(N,col=c("orange","green"),legend=T,args.legend = list(x=3, y=19, xjust=0, yjust=0.5), space=1)

# Histogramme non empile
barplot(N,col=c("orange","green"),legend=T, beside= T, main = "Title")

# Histogramme non empile en echangeant l'ordre des variables
barplot(t(N),col=c("orange","green","blue","grey","yellow"),legend=T, beside= T, main = "Title")
ChatGPT said:

This script analyzes the relationship between two qualitative variables ("sexe" and "transportTravail"):

  • table(sexe, transportTravail, ...) creates a contingency table between the two variables, including missing values.
  • addmargins(N) adds row and column totals to the table.
  • barplot(N, col=c(...), legend=T) generates stacked bar plots by default, with color and legend options.
  • barplot(N, beside=T, ...) creates side-by-side (non-stacked) bar plots.
  • barplot(t(N), ...) transposes the contingency table to switch the order of variables and then plots another side-by-side bar plot with different colors for each category.

You said:

"complete.obs"

What is thiis
ChatGPT said:

The "complete.obs" argument is used in correlation functions such as cor() to handle missing (NA) values in the dataset.

Explanation:

  • complete.obs: This argument tells the function to compute the correlation using only complete pairs of observations, i.e., it ignores any rows that have missing values (NA).

For example, if you want to calculate the correlation between two variables but some rows have missing data in one or both of the variables, complete.obs will exclude those rows from the calculation.

Example:

r
correlation = cor(pop$KILOMETRAGE, pop$DEPENSE, use = "complete.obs")
# Calcule la corrélation en utilisant seulement les lignes où KILOMETRAGE et DEPENSE ne sont pas manquants
  • Without "complete.obs", the function might return NA if there are any missing values. With "complete.obs", it skips the missing values and calculates the correlation based on the available data.
